Purple; A heat gun and a very patient me, it took two hours to heat up the steel to purple, but purple occupies such a small band on the temper color thing I couldn't risk missing it (and if I put the whole thing in a kiln, the temper of the ENTIRE blade would be ruined)

Blue: Oxi Acetylene torch, took like two seconds, was the easiest of all of them. 

Green: Brazed over section (brass rod), then treated with a nasty variety of chemicals to make it turn verdigris. This one was the hardest. 

Yellow: Brazed over section (brass rod) polished back to a high sheen.

Orange: Rust. Hydrogen peroxide, salt, vinegar. I THOUGHT this would be a lot easier than it was, it turns out that bright orange color is harder to achieve on purpose than you think, and I haven't found a way to seal it yet. Oil, wax, etc makes it darken. 

Red: Brazed over with Silicon Bronze, heated up and quenched with Borax. Also difficult. 

